[SHORT DESC]
Adds a chance of finding an item after each battle (no effect in battles).
[LONG DESC]
<p>After each battle, there is a 10% chance that a Pokémon with this ability may find an item. A Pokémon already holding an item cannot pick up another.</p>

<p>In Ruby and Sapphire, items that could be found by Pickup were the same regardless of the level of the user.</p>

<dl>

<dt>30%:</dt>
<dd>Super Potion</dd>

<dt>10%:</dt>
<dd>Ultra Ball, Full Restore, Full Heal, Nugget, Revive, Rare Candy</dd>

<dt>5%:</dt>
<dd>Protein</dd>

<dt>4%:</dt>
<dd>PP Up</dd>

<dt>1%:</dt>
<dd>King's Rock</dd>

</dl>

<p>In Leaf Green and Fire Red, items were also found regardless of the level of the user.</p>

<dl>

<dt>15%:</dt>
<dd>Oran Berry</dd>

<dt>10%:</dt>
<dd>Aspear Berry, Cheri Berry, Chesto Berry, Pecha Berry, Persim Berry, Rawst Berry</dd>

<dt>5%:</dt>
<dd>Nugget, PP Up, Rare Candy, TM 10 (Hidden Power)</dd>

<dt>1%:</dt>
<dd>Belue Berry, Durin Berry, Pamtre Berry, Spelon Berry, Watmel Berry</dd>

</dl>

<p>In Emerald, the probability of finding specific items changes with the user's level. A higher level user will have a better chance of receiving a rare item, as follows:</p>

